<hr data-start="3862" data-end="3865">
<h2 data-section-id="k4crtd" data-start="3867" data-end="3943">Since you're learning GitHub from scratch, here's a simple learning path:</h2>
<ol data-start="3945" data-end="4232">
<li data-section-id="5mqi7k" data-start="3945" data-end="3974">
<p data-start="3948" data-end="3974">✅ Create a GitHub account.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="xwu095" data-start="3975" data-end="3992">
<p data-start="3978" data-end="3992">✅ Install Git.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1i5wsu" data-start="3993" data-end="4051">
<p data-start="3996" data-end="4051">✅ Upload your <strong data-start="4010" data-end="4042">Blood Bank Management System</strong> project.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="16hz5uu" data-start="4052" data-end="4135">
<p data-start="4055" data-end="4135">✅ Learn how to update an existing project (<code data-start="4098" data-end="4107">git add</code>, <code data-start="4109" data-end="4121">git commit</code>, <code data-start="4123" data-end="4133">git push</code>).</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1azzj2t" data-start="4136" data-end="4187">
<p data-start="4139" data-end="4187">✅ Learn how to clone repositories (<code data-start="4174" data-end="4185">git clone</code>).</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1079t4x" data-start="4188" data-end="4232">
<p data-start="4191" data-end="4232">✅ Learn about branches and pull requests.</p>
</li>
</ol>
