<ul data-start="71" data-end="530">
<li data-section-id="1giam46" data-start="71" data-end="335">
<p data-start="73" data-end="335"><strong data-start="73" data-end="141">If you want to showcase your work to recruiters or interviewers:</strong> Don't upload only the report. It's much better to upload the <strong data-start="203" data-end="218">source code</strong>, the <strong data-start="224" data-end="234">report</strong>, and a <strong data-start="242" data-end="255">README.md</strong> file that explains the project. This shows that you actually built the project.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1x8q20q" data-start="337" data-end="530">
<p data-start="339" data-end="530"><strong data-start="339" data-end="371">If you only have the report:</strong> You can upload just the report (for example, <code data-start="417" data-end="458">Blood_Bank_Management_System_Report.pdf</code>). However, it won't demonstrate your programming skills as effectively.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="532" data-end="610">For your <strong data-start="541" data-end="573">Blood Bank Management System</strong> mini project, I recommend uploading:</p>
