)); --oai-wb-selection: var(--wb-selection,var(--theme-user-selection-bg,var(--selection,#93c5fd))); --oai-wb-radius: var(--wb-radius,1.5rem); --oai-wb-radius-sm: var(--wb-radius-sm,0.5rem); --oai-wb-shadow: var(--wb-shadow,0 4px 80px rgb(0 0 0/2%)); --oai-wb-shadow-lg: var(--wb-shadow-lg,0 10px 30px rgb(0 0 0/12%)); --oai-wb-font-sans: var(--wb-font-sans,var(--font-sans,sans-serif)); --oai-wb-font-mono: var(--wb-font-mono,var(--font-mono,monospace)); --oai-wb-font-size: var(--wb-font-size,0.875rem); --oai-wb-shimmer-dark-contrast: var(--wb-shimmer-dark-contrast,var(--oai-wb-text-tertiary)); --oai-wb-shimmer-dark-secondary: var(--wb-shimmer-dark-secondary,var(--oai-wb-text-tertiary)); --writing-block-editor-pt: calc(8 * var(--spacing)); --writing-block-editor-pr: calc(20 * var(--spacing)); --writing-block-editor-pb: calc(16 * var(--spacing)); --writing-block-editor-pl: calc(20 * var(--spacing));"><div class="outline-none data-[writing-block-fullscreen-editor]:min-h-[75vh] ProseMirror markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full min-h-6 break-words focus:outline-none" data-writing-block-fullscreen-editor-region="true" data-writing-block-fullscreen-editor-layout="inline" contenteditable="true" aria-disabled="false" dir="auto" translate="no"><h1><span>🩸 Blood Bank Management System</span></h1><p><span>A </span><strong><span>Database Management System (DBMS)</span></strong><span> mini project developed using </span><strong><span>MySQL</span></strong><span> to efficiently manage blood bank operations. The system stores and manages donor details, patient records, blood inventory, donations, and blood requests in a structured relational database.</span></p><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>📌 Project Overview</span></h2><p><span>The Blood Bank Management System is designed to automate the manual process of managing blood donations and blood requests. It provides a centralized database for maintaining donor information, patient details, blood stock, donation history, and request status.</span></p><p><span>The system ensures accurate blood inventory management by automatically updating stock after donations and approved blood requests.</span></p><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>🎯 Objectives</span></h2><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Automate blood bank record management.</span></p></li><li><p><span>Maintain donor and patient information.</span></p></li><li><p><span>Track blood stock in real time.</span></p></li><li><p><span>Process blood donations and requests efficiently.</span></p></li><li><p><span>Reduce manual errors and paperwork.</span></p></li><li><p><span>Generate useful reports for administrators.</span></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>✨ Features</span></h2><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>👤 Donor Management</span></p></li><li><p><span>🏥 Patient Management</span></p></li><li><p><span>🩸 Blood Stock Management</span></p></li><li><p><span>❤️ Blood Donation Tracking</span></p></li><li><p><span>📋 Blood Request Processing</span></p></li><li><p><span>🔄 Automatic Blood Stock Updates</span></p></li><li><p><span>📊 Inventory Monitoring</span></p></li><li><p><span>🔍 Blood Availability Search</span></p></li><li><p><span>📑 Donation History</span></p></li><li><p><span>📈 SQL Reports and Queries</span></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>🛠 Technologies Used</span></h2><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>MySQL</span></p></li><li><p><span>SQL</span></p></li><li><p><span>Database Management System (DBMS)</span></p></li><li><p><span>MySQL Workbench</span></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>📂 Project Structure</span></h2><pre dir="ltr"><code dir="ltr"><span>Blood-Bank-Management-System
│
├── README.md
├── LICENSE
├── .gitignore
│
├── database
│   ├── schema.sql
│   ├── insert_data.sql
│   ├── queries.sql
│   ├── triggers.sql
│   └── views.sql
│
├── report
│   └── BloodBankManagementSystem.pdf
│
├── screenshots
│   ├── donor_table.png
│   ├── patient_table.png
│   ├── blood_stock.png
│   ├── donation_table.png
│   └── blood_request_table.png
│
└── docs
    └── ER_Diagram.png</span></code></pre><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>🗄 Database Tables</span></h2><p><span>The project consists of the following main tables:</span></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Donor</span></p></li><li><p><span>Patient</span></p></li><li><p><span>BloodStock</span></p></li><li><p><span>Donation</span></p></li><li><p><span>BloodRequest</span></p></li></ul><p><span>These tables are connected using Primary Keys and Foreign Keys to maintain data integrity.</span></p><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>⚙️ How to Run the Project</span></h2><h3><span>Step 1</span></h3><p><span>Install </span><strong><span>MySQL</span></strong><span> and </span><strong><span>MySQL Workbench</span></strong><span>.</span></p><h3><span>Step 2</span></h3><p><span>Clone the repository.</span></p><pre dir="ltr"><code dir="ltr"><span>git clone https://github.com/yourusername/Blood-Bank-Management-System.git</span></code></pre><h3><span>Step 3</span></h3><p><span>Open MySQL Workbench.</span></p><h3><span>Step 4</span></h3><p><span>Execute the SQL files in the following order:</span></p><ol data-spread="false" start="1"><li><p><span>schema.sql</span></p></li><li><p><span>insert_data.sql</span></p></li><li><p><span>triggers.sql</span></p></li><li><p><span>views.sql</span></p></li><li><p><span>queries.sql</span></p></li></ol><h3><span>Step 5</span></h3><p><span>Run the sample SQL queries to view donor details, patient records, blood stock, donation history, and blood requests.</span></p><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>📊 Sample Reports</span></h2><p><span>The database can generate reports such as:</span></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Available Blood Stock</span></p></li><li><p><span>Donation History</span></p></li><li><p><span>Pending Blood Requests</span></p></li><li><p><span>Approved Requests</span></p></li><li><p><span>Low Stock Alert</span></p></li><li><p><span>Donor List</span></p></li><li><p><span>Patient List</span></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>🔮 Future Enhancements</span></h2><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Web-based interface</span></p></li><li><p><span>Mobile application</span></p></li><li><p><span>Email and SMS notifications</span></p></li><li><p><span>Hospital integration</span></p></li><li><p><span>User authentication</span></p></li><li><p><span>Role-based access control</span></p></li><li><p><span>Analytics dashboard</span></p></li><li><p><span>AI-based blood demand prediction</span></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>📷 Screenshots</span></h2><p><span>Add screenshots of:</span></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Donor Table</span></p></li><li><p><span>Patient Table</span></p></li><li><p><span>Blood Stock Table</span></p></li><li><p><span>Donation Table</span></p></li><li><p><span>Blood Request Table</span></p></li><li><p><span>ER Diagram</span></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>👩‍💻 Author</span></h2><p><strong><span>Ruchitha M</span></strong></p><p><span>Bachelor of Engineering</span><br><span>Information Science and Engineering</span><br><span>SJB Institute of Technology, Bengaluru</span></p><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>📄 License</span></h2><p><span>This project is intended for educational and academic purposes.</span></p></div></div></div><div data-writing-block-fullscreen-shell-border="true" aria-hidden="true" class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 rounded-[inherit] z-[2] [box-shadow:inset_0_0_0_1px_var(--oai-wb-border)] group-hover/writing-block-surface:[box-shadow:inset_0_0_0_1px_var(--oai-wb-border-hover)]"></div></div></div>
